<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="235" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1436,1302,1869]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">
Diagnosis. Glp-1 same level as Ds-1. Ds-2 on 
<collectingRegion box="[727,771,1338,1364]" country="Serbia" name="Ada" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">AD</collectingRegion>
. PE with 1 dorsal seta. GA tripartite in female, bipartite in male. Female with 6 Pgs and 4 Sgs. Male with 27–36 Pgs and 6 Sgs. Tf I–IV with 2-0-0-0 Bp setae; Gn I–IV with 2-1-0-0 Bp setae; Tb I–IV with 6-3-4-4 Bp setae; Ta I–IV with 1-1-0-0 Bp setae. Lc I with unidentate accessory process. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ausserer" authorityYear="1871" box="[249,353,1446,1472]" class="Arachnida" family="Idiopidae" genus="Idiosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="34" pageNumber="240" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Idiosoma</taxonomicName>
length 
<quantity box="[437,563,1446,1472]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.3185" metricValueMax="8.8138" metricValueMin="7.8232" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" unit="in" value="327.5" valueMax="347.0" valueMin="308.0">308–347 in</quantity>
female, 
<quantity box="[660,787,1446,1472]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.1153" metricValueMax="8.6614" metricValueMin="7.5691999999999995" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" unit="in" value="319.5" valueMax="341.0" valueMin="298.0">298–341 in</quantity>
male. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Krefft" authorityYear="1871" box="[861,1003,1446,1472]" class="Chromadorea" family="Gnathostomatidae" genus="Gnathosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spirurida" pageId="34" pageNumber="203" phylum="Nematoda" rank="genus">Gnathosoma</taxonomicName>
length 
<quantity box="[1086,1213,1446,1472]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.4229" metricValueMax="5.5118" metricValueMin="5.334" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" unit="in" value="213.5" valueMax="217.0" valueMin="210.0">210–217 in</quantity>
female, 
<quantity box="[1310,1436,1446,1472]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0673" metricValueMax="5.3086" metricValueMin="4.826" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" unit="in" value="199.5" valueMax="209.0" valueMin="190.0">190–209 in</quantity>
male. Ratio of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Krefft" authorityYear="1871" box="[318,453,1482,1508]" class="Chromadorea" family="Gnathostomatidae" genus="Gnathosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spirurida" pageId="34" pageNumber="203" phylum="Nematoda" rank="genus">gnathosoma</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ausserer" authorityYear="1871" box="[489,592,1482,1508]" class="Arachnida" family="Idiopidae" genus="Idiosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="34" pageNumber="240" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">idiosoma</taxonomicName>
0.62–0.69 in female, 0.60–0.64 in male.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1436,1302,1869]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">
Remarks. Bartsch (1986) noted that morphology and chaetotaxy of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Krefft" authorityYear="1871" box="[963,1098,1518,1544]" class="Chromadorea" family="Gnathostomatidae" genus="Gnathosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spirurida" pageId="34" pageNumber="203" phylum="Nematoda" rank="genus">gnathosoma</taxonomicName>
and legs coincided with those in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Andre" authorityYear="1961" box="[181,329,1554,1581]" class="Arachnida" family="Halacaridae" genus="Scaptognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabularius">
<emphasis box="[181,329,1554,1581]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">S. sabularius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The species resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Andre" authorityYear="1961" box="[606,753,1554,1581]" class="Arachnida" family="Halacaridae" genus="Scaptognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabularius">
<emphasis box="[606,753,1554,1581]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">S. sabularius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Trouessart" authorityYear="1894" box="[811,915,1554,1581]" class="Arachnida" family="Halacaridae" genus="Scaptognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hallezi">
<emphasis box="[811,915,1554,1581]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">S. hallezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from them by the tripartite GA in female and bipartite GA in male. Bartsch (1986) noted that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Trouessart" authorityYear="1894" box="[808,910,1590,1617]" class="Arachnida" family="Halacaridae" genus="Scaptognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hallezi">
<emphasis box="[808,910,1590,1617]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">S. hallezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
recorded by 
<bibRefCitation author="Morselli, I. &amp; Mari, M." box="[1054,1318,1590,1617]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" pagination="201 - 220" refId="ref49110" refString="Morselli, I. &amp; Mari, M. (1985) Recerche sugli Alacaridi delle coste Livornesi 4. Osservazioni su alcune specie raccolte su fondi sabbiosi della zona di Piombino. Atti della Societa Toscana di Scienze Naturali, Memorie, Serie B, 91, 201 - 220." type="journal article" year="1985">Morselli &amp; Mari (1985)</bibRefCitation>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1385,1436,1590,1616]" name="Italy" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">Italy</collectingCountry>
should refer to this species. The Italian record from Piombino may need further verification. Female and male are known.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1436,1302,1869]" box="[208,884,1698,1725]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">
Habitat. Sublittoral zone: Sandy sediment at 
<quantity box="[709,807,1698,1725]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="34" pageNumber="235" unit="m" value="28.0" valueMax="45.0" valueMin="11.0">11–45 m</quantity>
depth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1436,1302,1869]" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">
Distribution. Mediterranean: Île If, Île Ratonneau, Île Riou, Île Jarre, Morgiau, Port-Miau [
<collectingCountry box="[1225,1310,1734,1761]" name="France" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">France</collectingCountry>
]. Piombino [
<collectingCountry box="[158,217,1770,1797]" name="Italy" pageId="34" pageNumber="235">Italy</collectingCountry>
].
</paragraph>
